    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced leek</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Reboil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
