          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Tear the <strong>ciabatta<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>torn ciabatta</strong> to a baking tray lined with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Grate the <strong>remaining Italian hard cheese </strong>over the top and drizzle over a little of the <strong>ribollita base</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 8-10 min or until golden – these are your <strong>cheesy croutons</strong></p><p>Tip: Crowd the croutons together for the best melty cheese!</p>",
      "order": 5,
